article.headline: Valparaiso 68, Youngstown St. 57
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Urule Igbavboa scored 27 points and nine rebounds and Valparaiso pulled away in the second half to beat Youngstown State 68-57 Thursday night. Jake Diebler added 15 points, including four 3-pointers, for the Crusaders (3-4, 1-1 Horizon League). Kelvin Bright had 13 points for Youngstown State (1-5, 0-1). Sirlester Martin added 11 points and a game-high 11 rebounds, and DeAndre Mays scored 10. The Penguins were ahead 35-32 to start the second half, and the lead changed several times until the Crusaders took control for good when Logan Jones scored a layup at 13:04 to bring it to 40-39. Valparaiso scored 9 unanswered points to lead by 16 with 1:59 left to play. The Penguins were up by 14 with 5:00 to go in the first half after outscoring Valparaiso 8-0, but the Crusaders closed the gap to 3 when Diebler hit two 3-pointers to close out the period.
